# e71d2245a234416b87af97084566d573
#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/plugins/plugins_coordinate_capture.rst:14
msgid ""
"The coordinate capture plugin is easy to use and provides the ability to "
"display coordinates on the map canvas for two selected Coordinate Reference "
"Systems (CRS)."
msgstr ""

# 8487c182c4204b4f91773ef7e588bf5a
#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/plugins/plugins_coordinate_capture.rst:29
msgid ""
"Start QGIS, select |mActionOptions| :guilabel:`Project Properties` from the :"
"guilabel:`Settings` (KDE, Windows) or :guilabel:`File` (Gnome, OSX) menu and "
"click on the :guilabel:`Projection` tab. As an alternative you can also "
"click on the |mIconProjectionEnabled| :sup:`CRS status` icon in the lower "
"right-hand corner of the statusbar."
msgstr ""

# f0d2e56f4fd24b42ba480f75bc802a70
#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/plugins/plugins_coordinate_capture.rst:34
msgid ""
"Click on the |checkbox| `Enable on the fly projection` checkbox and select a "
"projected coordinate system of your choice (see also :ref:"
"`label_projections`)."
msgstr ""

# 538392a88518416088e181c75f7dc1ca
#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/plugins/plugins_coordinate_capture.rst:36
msgid ""
"Load the coordinate capture plugin in the Plugin Manager (see :ref:"
"`load_core_plugin`) and ensure that the dialog is visible by going to :"
"menuselection:`View --> Panels` and ensuring that |checkbox| :guilabel:"
"`Coordinate Capture` is enabled. The coordinate capture dialog appears as "
"shown in Figure figure_coordinate_capture_1_."
msgstr ""

# a88677dbb95240db81b2515348141c5c
#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/plugins/plugins_coordinate_capture.rst:41
msgid ""
"Click on the |geographic| :sup:`Click to the select the CRS to use for "
"coordinate display` icon and select a different CRS from the one you "
"selected above."
msgstr ""

# 04cce6773d9946ba8264a09892860c7f
#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/plugins/plugins_coordinate_capture.rst:44
msgid ""
"To start capturing coordinates, click on **[Start capture]**. You can now "
"click anywhere on the map canvas and the plugin will show the coordinates "
"for both of your selected CRS."
msgstr ""

# 15516188f309451eabf4d65a1625c131
#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/plugins/plugins_coordinate_capture.rst:47
msgid ""
"To enable mouse coordinate tracking click the |tracking| :sup:`mouse "
"tracking` icon."
msgstr ""

# 7f0a75163c9b4c719a4117c7aaba6a31
